narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: HEBR 158 is an excellent course to improve one's Hebrew (spoken and written) while learning more about Israeli society and culture. It is a well balanced course in terms of amount and type of workload, and was taught excellently by Professor Shiri Goren.
A good way to keep up your hebrew and improve it. Entertaining.

This is a fantastic course for anyone interested in looking at society through the lens of film or just interested in Israeli film. Shiri is a fantastic teacher and always available to talk about the material and make sure students feel engaged and comfortable in class. Highly recommend this class.
